<br>
Basically I see Keep raids pointless untill Mythic changes the way we take them and make taking a keep a MONUMENTAL task to do.<br>
<br>
Currently, you only need 20 people and about 20 minutes..!  Every keep becomes a trivial task.. with no strategy needed.<br>
<br>
You gain NOTHING for a taking at keep.  No exp, no Realm points..  and the minute you leave it is taken back.<br>
<br>
I will be suggesting to Mythic that that increase the requirments to take a keep.<br>
<br>
1) All keeps guards lvl's increased by 5 <br>
<br>
2) Any keep door upgraded to lvl 8+ cannot be defeated without the use of a Ram.<br>
<br>
3) Any keep flying a flag for more than a week gains Robed Caster as defenders. (for the added ability of small AE DD's, AE Mez's.. etc)  This will add to the stategy of taking such a keep.<br>
<br>
The purpose/point of this is that Keeps shouldn't trade hands 4-5 times in one day.  They should stand for weeks and be a MONUMENTAL EPIC BATTLE of massive proportion to take a Realm Keep.<br>
<br>
Thus, when a Keep is finally flying your Realms flag you all can stand back and be proud of the accomplishment/allied victory. Not log on 2 hours later and find that is was alreadyt taken back.<br>
<br>
Keep=Dragon, IMO<br>
